<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="152" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1451,226,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,241,226,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="152">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="M. D. Miranda &amp; E. L. Jacques. A, Abaxial" authorityYear="2022" box="[248,418,227,248]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="5" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="umbrosa">
<emphasis box="[248,418,227,248]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="152">Begonia umbrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Irmsch (1953: 41)" authorityName="Irmsch. A, Mature" authorityPageNumber="41" authorityYear="1953" box="[622,1003,227,249]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="5" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cornitepala">
<emphasis box="[622,819,227,248]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="152">Begonia cornitepala</emphasis>
Irmsch (1953: 41)
</taxonomicName>
. It differs chiefly in having peltate leaf blades (
<emphasis box="[197,217,263,284]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="152">vs</emphasis>
. basifixed) and pauciflorus cymes (
<emphasis box="[561,581,263,284]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="152">vs</emphasis>
. multiflorus).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
